CMakeLists: add a WITH_SYSTEM_LZMA option beside WITH_SYSTEM_ZLIB/ZSTD

Upstream unconditionally vendors the 7-Zip LZMA SDK (deps/lzma-25.01,
built as the private static chdr-lzma target and folded into libchdr.so)
-- unlike zlib and zstd, for which the maintainer already provides
WITH_SYSTEM_ZLIB / WITH_SYSTEM_ZSTD options (his own CHANGELOG.md 0.3.0
notes: "for distros"). This image ships the same SDK as a real shared
library (BR2_EXTERNAL sibling package/lzma-sdk: liblzma-sdk.so plus an
lzma-sdk.pc), and the no-vendoring policy wants libchdr linked against
that instead of carrying a second private copy of the identical decoder.

This adds the missing third option, deliberately mirroring the
WITH_SYSTEM_ZSTD block's structure and variable flow: the system branch
resolves the dependency and appends the imported target to PLATFORM_LIBS
plus a CHDR_SYSTEM_LZMA compile definition to CHDR_DEFINES (exactly how
the zstd branch appends zstd::zstd / CHDR_SYSTEM_ZSTD); the else branch
is upstream's bundled block, content-identical (each line reindented two
spaces inside the else(), matching the WITH_SYSTEM_ZSTD else block's
formatting) and still the default (OFF), so plain upstream builds are
unaffected. The one necessary difference
from the zstd block: there is no find_package() module or CMake config
package for the LZMA SDK anywhere (the SDK upstream ships no build
system at all), so the probe is pkg-config's IMPORTED_TARGET against
lzma-sdk.pc -- the same fallback mechanism upstream itself reached for
in commit 23d3ddd ("cmake: fallback to pkgconfig if the zstd cmake
config is missing") when zstd's CMake config package proved unreliable
across distros. CHDR_SYSTEM_LZMA is consumed by the companion patches
0002/0003, which switch src/codec_lzma.h to the system <LzmaDec.h>.

Upstream status: follows the maintainer's own WITH_SYSTEM_* pattern
(added "for distros" per CHANGELOG); candidate for upstreaming, not yet
sent.

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -8,6 +8,7 @@ endif()
 option(INSTALL_STATIC_LIBS "Install static libraries" OFF)
 option(WITH_SYSTEM_ZLIB "Use system provided zlib library" OFF)
 option(WITH_SYSTEM_ZSTD "Use system provided zstd library" OFF)
+option(WITH_SYSTEM_LZMA "Use system provided lzma-sdk library" OFF)
 option(CHDR_WANT_RAW_DATA_SECTOR "Output ECC data and sync header" ON)
 option(CHDR_WANT_SUBCODE "Output CD subchannel data" ON)
 option(CHDR_VERIFY_BLOCK_CRC "Verify integrity of decoded data" ON)
@@ -38,10 +39,17 @@ include(GNUInstallDirs)
 #--------------------------------------------------
 
 # lzma
-if(NOT TARGET chdr-lzma)
-  add_subdirectory(deps/lzma-25.01 EXCLUDE_FROM_ALL)
+if (WITH_SYSTEM_LZMA)
+  find_package(PkgConfig REQUIRED)
+  pkg_check_modules(LZMASDK REQUIRED IMPORTED_TARGET lzma-sdk)
+  list(APPEND PLATFORM_LIBS PkgConfig::LZMASDK)
+  list(APPEND CHDR_DEFINES CHDR_SYSTEM_LZMA)
+else()
+  if(NOT TARGET chdr-lzma)
+    add_subdirectory(deps/lzma-25.01 EXCLUDE_FROM_ALL)
+  endif()
+  list(APPEND CHDR_LIBS chdr-lzma)
 endif()
-list(APPEND CHDR_LIBS chdr-lzma)
 
 # zlib
 if (WITH_SYSTEM_ZLIB)
